Instructions

- When typing in user input into the program the controller can read a line of 3-4 inputs with spaces in between.
- All inputs are case-insensitive
- To quit the program simply type "quit" on its own line (case-insensitive)
- All command lines MUST be 3-4 inputs long or "quit", or the program will do nothing while waiting for more inputs
- If an invalid command is entered the program will display "Invalid command please try again"

Valid 3 Input Command Lines
- "load image-path image-name"
- Load an image from the specified path and refer it to henceforth in the program by the given image name.

- "save image-path image-name"
- Save the image with the given name to the specified path which should include the name of the file.

- "red-component image-name dest-image-name"
- Create a greyscale image with the red-component of the image with the given name, and refer to it henceforth in the
- program by the given destination name. Similar commands for green, blue, value, luma, intensity are also supported
- in the same format of the keyword-component as the first input.

- "horizontal-flip image-name dest-image-name"
- Flip an image horizontally to create a new image, referred to henceforth by the given destination name.

- "vertical-flip image-name dest-image-name"
- Flip an image vertically to create a new image, referred to henceforth by the given destination name.

- "blur image-name dest-image-name"
- Create a blurred image with the given name, and refer to it henceforth in the program by the given destination name.

- "sharpen image-name dest-image-name"
- Create a sharpened image with the given name, and refer to it henceforth in the program by the given destination name.

- "sepia image-name dest-image-name"
- Create a sepia-toned image with the given name,
- and refer to it henceforth in the program by the given destination name.

- "greyscale image-name dest-image-name"
- Create a greyscale image with the given name, and refer to it henceforth in the program by the given destination name.

Valid 4 Input Command Lines
- "brighten increment image-name dest-image-name"
- Brighten the image by the given increment to create a new image, referred to henceforth by the given destination name.
- The increment must be positive and the new RGB values will be capped at 255

- "darken increment image-name dest-image-name"
- Darken the image by the given increment to create a new image, referred to henceforth by the given destination name.
- The increment must be positive and the new RGB values will be capped at 0

Valid 1 Input Command Lines
- "quit"
- Immediately quits the program

GUI Instructions

- Click the load button to be prompted to select a file
- Choose your file and open it
- The loaded image and its histograms will appear on the screen
- Then select what edits you would like to apply to your image from the drop-down menu
- After selecting the desired edit click the apply button
- The changed image and its histograms will appear on the screen
- Whenever you are done editing the image click the save button
- You will be prompted to name your file and select a location to save it to
- Click save